HEADWORD: Culdee
<hw>Cul*dee"</hw> <pr>(k<?/l-d<?/" ⟦or⟧ k<?/l"d<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[ Prob. fr. Gael.<ets>cuilteach</ets>; cf. Ir.
<ets>ceilede</ets>.]</ety> <def>One of a class of anchorites who lived
in various parts of Scotland, Ireland, and Wales.</def>⟦br⟧
